    <main class="main-panel">
      <div class="page-header-area">
        <h1 class="page-title">Border</h1>
        <p class="page-desc">Use borders to define boundaries, communicate interaction states, and improve scan clarity across endpoint workflows.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="main-content-area">
        <div class="main-content-inner">


          <!-- Border principles -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="border-principles">
            <h2>Border principles</h2>

            <div style="margin-top: 24px;">
              <h3 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 12px;">1. Borders communicate boundaries</h3>
              <p style="color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; max-width: 800px;">
                Borders should separate meaningfully different content regions. Do not use borders where whitespace already creates clear grouping.
              </p>
              <div style="margin-top: 16px; padding: 20px 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                <div style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 10px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">Good use cases</div>
                <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px;">
                  <span style="font-size: 13px; padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.08); color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 500;">Table row separators</span>
                  <span style="font-size: 13px; padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.08); color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 500;">Filter sidebar edges</span>
                  <span style="font-size: 13px; padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.08); color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 500;">Drawer boundaries</span>
                  <span style="font-size: 13px; padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.08); color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 500;">Destructive confirmation zones</span>
                  <span style="font-size: 13px; padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.08); color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 500;">Widget containers</span>
                  <span style="font-size: 13px; padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.08); color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 500;">Split troubleshooting panes</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 32px;">
              <h3 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 12px;">2. Pair width and color tokens</h3>
              <p style="color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; max-width: 800px;">
                Prism borders are always created by combining a <strong style="color: var(--prism-text);">width token</strong> and a <strong style="color: var(--prism-text);">semantic color token</strong>. A border without semantic meaning becomes visual noise.
              </p>
              <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 16px; margin-top: 16px;">
                <div style="padding: 20px 24px; background: rgba(12, 136, 68, 0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(12, 136, 68, 0.2); border-radius: 12px;">
                  <div style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: #0c8844; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; margin-bottom: 10px;">✓ Good</div>
                  <code style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-text); line-height: 1.8; display: block;">border.width.default + color.border.subtle<br>border.width.selected + color.border.selected<br>border.width.focused + color.border.focused</code>
                </div>
                <div style="padding: 20px 24px; background: rgba(228, 37, 39, 0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(228, 37, 39, 0.2); border-radius: 12px;">
                  <div style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: #e42527; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; margin-bottom: 10px;">✗ Bad</div>
                  <code style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-text); line-height: 1.8; display: block;">border: 1px solid #ccc<br>border: 2px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1)<br>border-bottom: 1px solid gray</code>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Border width tokens -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="border-width">
            <h2>Border width tokens</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 12px; max-width: 800px;">
              Width tokens define the thickness of borders. These come from the <strong style="color: var(--prism-text);">UEMS Global Tokens</strong> collection and are consistent across all themes.
            </p>
            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 20px; font-size: 14px;">
              <thead>
                <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--prism-border);">
                  <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-text); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">Token</th>
                  <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-text); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">Value</th>
                  <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-text); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">Preview</th>
                  <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-text); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">Usage</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><code style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-violet);">border-width-0</code></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">0px</td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><div style="width: 80px; height: 0; border-top: 0px solid var(--prism-text-muted);"></div></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-size: 13px;">No border — reset/remove</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><code style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-violet);">border-width-1</code></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">1px</td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><div style="width: 80px; height: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--prism-text-muted);"></div></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-size: 13px;">Default — table rows, cards, dividers</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><code style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-violet);">border-width-2</code></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">2px</td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><div style="width: 80px; height: 0; border-top: 2px solid var(--prism-text-muted);"></div></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-size: 13px;">Emphasis — selected, focused, active states</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <!-- Border radius tokens -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="border-radius">
            <h2>Border radius tokens</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 12px; max-width: 800px;">
              Radius tokens control corner rounding. These are also part of the <strong style="color: var(--prism-text);">UEMS Global Tokens</strong> collection. Use them for consistent shape language across all components.
            </p>
            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 20px; font-size: 14px;">
              <thead>
                <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--prism-border);">
                  <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-text); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">Token</th>
                  <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-text); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">Value</th>
                  <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-text); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">Preview</th>
                  <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-text); font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">Usage</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><code style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-violet);">radius-2</code></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">2px</td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><div style="width: 40px; height: 40px; border: 2px solid var(--prism-violet); border-radius: 2px;"></div></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-size: 13px;">Micro — checkboxes, inline tags</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><code style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-violet);">radius-4</code></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">4px</td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><div style="width: 40px; height: 40px; border: 2px solid var(--prism-violet); border-radius: 4px;"></div></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-size: 13px;">Small — inputs, small buttons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><code style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-violet);">radius-6</code></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">6px</td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><div style="width: 40px; height: 40px; border: 2px solid var(--prism-violet); border-radius: 6px;"></div></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-size: 13px;">Default — buttons, dropdowns, cards</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><code style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-violet);">radius-8</code></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">8px</td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><div style="width: 40px; height: 40px; border: 2px solid var(--prism-violet); border-radius: 8px;"></div></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-size: 13px;">Medium — cards, panels, modals</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><code style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-violet);">radius-12</code></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">12px</td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px;"><div style="width: 40px; height: 40px; border: 2px solid var(--prism-violet); border-radius: 12px;"></div></td>
                  <td style="padding: 14px 16px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-size: 13px;">Large — dialogs, drawers</td>
