          <!-- Border color tokens - Structural -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="structural-borders">
            <h2>Structural border colors</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 12px; max-width: 800px;">
              Structural borders define layout boundaries — table rows, card edges, panel dividers, and disabled states. These are the most commonly used border tokens.
            </p>
            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 20px; font-size: 14px;">
              <thead>
                <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--prism-border);">
